  "prompt": "What is pork gelatin?",
  "response": "Pork gelatin is a gelling agent derived from the collagen found in the skin, bones, and connective tissues of pigs. It is commonly used in food products such as candies (e.g., gummy bears), marshmallows, and desserts (e.g., gelatin desserts like Jell-O), as well as in pharmaceuticals, cosmetics, and other industrial applications. The gelatin is processed to form a flavorless and transparent substance that can thicken, stabilize, or texturize products. It is not suitable for vegetarian, vegan, or certain religious dietary restrictions, such as kosher or halal diets, unless specially certified.",
